OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FUS Army clears convictions 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fof 110 black soldiers      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The US Army has overturned convictions 
OL,6, of 110 black soldiers who were arrested
OL,7, after the 1917 Houston Riots.          
OL,9,FA military review found the soldiers   
OL,10,Fwere not given fair trials and were    
OL,11,F"wrongly treated" because of their     
OL,12,Frace.                                  
OL,14,FRecords will now be reclassified to    
OL,15,Fcharacterise their military service as 
OL,16,Fhonourable.                            
OL,18,FThe riots took place after months of   
OL,19,Fracial provocations against members of 
OL,20,Fa regiment known as "Buffalo Soldiers".
